news.title: Nagpur: Rising steel prices due to war may make homes costlier, say builders
news.para: The builders claim that it may ultimately lead to an increase of 20% to 30% in the selling price of real estate in new projects.

news.title: Government will sanction more houses for Dharwad: Karnataka housing minister
news.para: During the bhoomi puja for the construction work of 235 houses in Kundagol town on Saturday, Somanna said 4,075 houses have already been sanctioned to urban areas of the district.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA races against time to finish one-cent layouts
news.para: The VMRDA is developing 56 layouts on about 4,000 acres in different parts of Visakhapatnam district for distribution of house sites to about 1.8 lakh homeless poor.

news.title: Draw of lots for over 110 flats in Greater Noida
news.para: Officials from the authority said that the first draw will be among applicants who have opted for lump sum payment. After that, there will be a draw among the applicants opting for payment in instalments.

news.title: Over 125 commercial projects under construction in Nashik
news.para: Earlier, commercial projects were limited only to posh commercial market areas like College Road, Mahatma Nagar, M G Road and Main Road areas of the city. But now the projects are coming up at Mhasrul, Adgaon, Pathardi, Untawadi, Govind Nagar and Indira Nagar.

news.title: No MOFA rights to flat purchasers on project on MMRDA land: Bombay HC
news.para: The Court held that the MMRDA Act expressly excludes the applicability of MOFA entirely from lands belonging to or vested in MMRDA.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Builder's son, nephew arrested in Rs 100 crore realty fraud
news.para: On March 1, developer Rajkumar Jain and his four family members, who had been living in Delhi under assumed names, were arrested by the Ghaziabad police.

news.title: Cement companies assure Tamil Nadu government to contain costs
news.para: The assurance comes in the wake of reports over an unprecedented spike in the cost of various construction materials including cement in the past two years and adversely impacting individual builders and developers.

news.title: About 380 stalled SRA projects to be revived by amnesty scheme in Mumbai
news.para: A recent SRA review report revealed that 380 SRA projects have been stuck or dead since 2005. These have not taken off and are stuck at various stages of development, and in many cases slum dwellers who have been evicted are living on rent.

news.title: Mumbai: Mahavir Developers booked for noise pollution rules breach
news.para: Pandey warned developers that failure to follow the rules could attract Indian Penal Code (IPC) sections.

news.title: Delhi police file FIR against M3M India, others in land row
news.para: The FIR was lodged following a complaint against these companies by real estate major, MGF. In January this year, an FIR was registered against MGF in Gurugram after M3M and the others moved a petition in a local court.

news.title: Pune IGR to digitise old property papers stored as photo films
news.para: A proposal for this will be sent to the government after discussion with technical experts, stated Inspector General of Registration and Stamps (IGR) Shravan Hardikar.

news.title: A month on, no FIR yet in Rs 50 crore C&D waste fraud in Gurugram
news.para: After a heated exchange between the MCG commissioner, councillors and mayor on the former refusing to share the report of the alleged fraud on February 24, it was decided that action would be against the firm even though a probe by the committee formed by the state government is under way.

news.title: New Town Kolkata development body opens property tax camp
news.para: NKDA officials said they were receiving complaints from people who were facing problems while paying tax online and that many were receiving notices demanding double payment.

news.title: Family feud breaks out at Analjit Singh's Max Group
news.para: In submissions made through her advocates at a hearing before the tribunal, Neelu Analjit Singh, who owns a 24.1% stake in Max Ventures & Investment Holding, claimed that the assets of the family holding company were being alienated to the detriment of her interests and information about the co's affairs was being withheld from her.
